WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.440
We'll turn tonight to Isaiah in chapter 41.

00:00:03.440 --> 00:00:06.639
Isaiah in chapter 41.

00:00:06.639 --> 00:00:09.000
And verse number, for the sake of time tonight,

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:13.399
we'll just read from verse 17 down to verse 20.

00:00:13.399 --> 00:00:21.000
Isaiah 41, reading from verse 17 down to verse 20.

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:23.500
We'll hear God's word this evening.

00:00:23.500 --> 00:00:28.739
When the poor and needy seek water, and there is none,

00:00:28.860 --> 00:00:31.700
and their tongue faileth for thirst,

00:00:31.700 --> 00:00:34.380
I, the Lord, will hear them.

00:00:34.380 --> 00:00:37.740
I, the God of Israel, will not forsake them.

00:00:37.740 --> 00:00:41.580
I will open rivers in high places,

00:00:41.580 --> 00:00:44.819
and fountains in the midst of the valleys.

00:00:44.819 --> 00:00:48.380
I will make the wilderness a pool of water,

00:00:48.380 --> 00:00:51.700
and the dry land springs of water.

00:00:51.700 --> 00:00:56.779
I will plant in the wilderness the cedar, the shitar tree,

00:00:56.779 --> 00:01:01.540
the myrtle, the oil tree, and I will set in the desert

00:01:01.540 --> 00:01:05.300
the fir tree and the pine, the box tree together,

00:01:05.300 --> 00:01:09.660
that they may see, and know, and consider,

00:01:09.660 --> 00:01:13.019
and understand together that the hand of the Lord

00:01:13.019 --> 00:01:19.300
hath done this, and the Holy One of Israel hath created it.

00:01:19.300 --> 00:01:19.800
Amen.

00:01:19.800 --> 00:01:22.339
And we know the Lord will bless the reading of his word

00:01:22.339 --> 00:01:23.620
tonight.

00:01:23.620 --> 00:01:26.739
Let's just pray together briefly before we look at God's

00:01:26.739 --> 00:01:28.059
word.

00:01:28.059 --> 00:01:31.019
Almighty God, we turn to thee.

00:01:31.019 --> 00:01:33.059
The arm of flesh will fail us.

00:01:33.059 --> 00:01:35.500
We dare not trust our own.

00:01:35.500 --> 00:01:38.779
But we do tonight put on the gospel armor.

00:01:38.779 --> 00:01:40.900
And we do watch unto prayer.

00:01:40.900 --> 00:01:43.500
And we do ask thee, Lord, as we've been singing,

00:01:43.500 --> 00:01:46.900
make us ready for the coming of the Lord Jesus.

00:01:46.900 --> 00:01:49.419
And Lord, we thank thee for thy word tonight.

00:01:49.419 --> 00:01:52.220
We thank thee for this church, for the pastor and this church.

00:01:52.220 --> 00:01:54.860
And we pray you bless him and his family,

00:01:54.860 --> 00:01:58.260
and bless each member of this congregation here this evening.

00:01:58.260 --> 00:02:00.779
Or may they know thy presence in a very real way.

00:02:00.779 --> 00:02:04.660
May you speak to us, encourage us in the things of God.

00:02:04.660 --> 00:02:06.819
We pray that thy spirit would speak tonight

00:02:06.819 --> 00:02:09.220
through the preaching of the word.

00:02:09.220 --> 00:02:12.699
We pray that, Lord, hearts would be surrendered to thee.

00:02:12.699 --> 00:02:14.899
And we ask this in Jesus' name.

00:02:14.899 --> 00:02:17.259
Amen.

00:02:17.259 --> 00:02:20.580
The book of Isaiah is found here in the middle of the Bible.

00:02:20.580 --> 00:02:22.860
And in my country, we say Isaiah.

00:02:22.860 --> 00:02:25.059
I know here it's Isaiah.

00:02:25.059 --> 00:02:28.020
And so you have to forgive me if you don't understand what I'm saying.

00:02:28.020 --> 00:02:30.300
You just have to nod along, OK?

00:02:30.300 --> 00:02:32.779
But the book of Isaiah is found in the middle of the Bible.

00:02:32.779 --> 00:02:35.779
And oftentimes, people call it the mini Bible.

00:02:35.779 --> 00:02:37.699
There are 66 books in the Bible.

00:02:37.699 --> 00:02:41.059
And there are 66 chapters here in Isaiah.

00:02:41.059 --> 00:02:44.339
And if you were to read from verse chapter number one

00:02:44.339 --> 00:02:46.259
down to chapter number 39,

00:02:46.259 --> 00:02:49.339
you'd find much of the first part of Isaiah

00:02:49.339 --> 00:02:53.380
to be all about woe and difficulty and cursing.

00:02:53.380 --> 00:02:55.539
And then you get to chapter 40,

00:02:55.539 --> 00:02:59.940
and you find the first word of chapter 40 is the word comfort.

00:02:59.940 --> 00:03:03.500
Because that's the New Testament, some people say,

00:03:03.500 --> 00:03:05.899
when the Lord Jesus Christ will come.

00:03:05.899 --> 00:03:06.940
Comfort.

00:03:06.940 --> 00:03:07.779
And he did come.

00:03:07.779 --> 00:03:08.979
And he has come.

00:03:08.979 --> 00:03:13.020
And he has brought great comfort to men and women around the world.

00:03:13.020 --> 00:03:15.660
Here we are in Isaiah chapter 41 tonight.

00:03:15.660 --> 00:03:19.300
And the Bible has told us in the book of Isaiah

00:03:19.300 --> 00:03:21.860
that judgment is coming

00:03:21.860 --> 00:03:24.979
and that judgment will come to the people of God

00:03:24.979 --> 00:03:26.979
because they, particularly in Isaiah,

00:03:26.979 --> 00:03:29.740
have fallen into idolatry.

00:03:29.740 --> 00:03:32.820
If you read Isaiah 40 in verse 18,

00:03:32.820 --> 00:03:34.139
the Bible says this,

00:03:34.139 --> 00:03:37.139
to whom then will you liken God?

00:03:37.139 --> 00:03:41.539
Or what likeness will you compare unto him?

00:03:41.539 --> 00:03:44.539
And there are many people in the time of Isaiah

00:03:44.539 --> 00:03:47.339
who were making their own God.

00:03:47.339 --> 00:03:51.779
And the Lord says, the nations are like a bucket.

00:03:51.779 --> 00:03:55.139
And the Bible tells us that there were people

00:03:55.139 --> 00:03:57.100
who were making all kinds of gods.

00:03:57.100 --> 00:03:59.539
And then the Bible says in verse 21,

00:03:59.539 --> 00:04:01.100
have you not known?

00:04:01.100 --> 00:04:02.500
Have you not heard?

00:04:02.500 --> 00:04:04.860
Have you not been told you from the beginning?

00:04:04.860 --> 00:04:09.259
Have you not understood from the foundations of the earth?

00:04:09.259 --> 00:04:13.179
It is he that sitteth upon the circle of the earth.

00:04:13.179 --> 00:04:16.779
And so the Bible message of Isaiah really

00:04:16.779 --> 00:04:21.339
is to behold our God, to look to God.

00:04:21.339 --> 00:04:23.339
And I just want to draw your attention tonight

00:04:23.339 --> 00:04:25.700
with God's help to a little expression here

00:04:25.700 --> 00:04:29.059
that I believe Isaiah is giving by the Holy Spirit

00:04:29.059 --> 00:04:32.059
to the people of God, the true people of God

00:04:32.059 --> 00:04:34.100
who are living in captivity.

00:04:34.100 --> 00:04:36.820
And it's found here in verse number 17.

00:04:36.820 --> 00:04:38.459
Look with me there if you can.

00:04:38.459 --> 00:04:40.739
Just a little expression and it says this,

00:04:40.739 --> 00:04:43.380
I the Lord.

00:04:43.380 --> 00:04:45.779
And I want to speak tonight with God's help

00:04:45.779 --> 00:04:49.859
just simply about that thought, I the Lord.

00:04:49.859 --> 00:04:54.059
That is what the whole world just needs to see.

00:04:54.059 --> 00:04:56.700
But can I say before the world can see it,

00:04:56.700 --> 00:04:58.700
you have to see it.

00:04:58.700 --> 00:05:02.019
Before the world, before this community can see

00:05:02.019 --> 00:05:05.500
I the Lord in their life,

00:05:05.500 --> 00:05:07.299
it has to begin with us, doesn't it?

00:05:08.299 --> 00:05:10.380
And so I want to begin there with God's help.

00:05:11.019 --> 00:05:12.140
And I want you to see this evening

00:05:12.140 --> 00:05:16.660
that the work of God begins really with the Lord.

00:05:16.660 --> 00:05:18.140
It doesn't begin with me.

00:05:18.140 --> 00:05:20.619
It doesn't begin with you.

00:05:20.619 --> 00:05:25.220
I didn't choose for myself to go to the country of Wales.

00:05:25.220 --> 00:05:29.899
I'm an Englishman and an Englishman likes his own castle.

00:05:29.899 --> 00:05:30.899
That's what they say, isn't it?

00:05:30.899 --> 00:05:32.019
Or castle.

00:05:32.019 --> 00:05:34.220
They like their own castle.

00:05:34.220 --> 00:05:37.179
But I didn't choose to go to where God chose.

00:05:38.140 --> 00:05:40.299
And I want to say to you my friend this evening,

00:05:41.220 --> 00:05:42.660
if we were to sum up our lives, it should be this.

00:05:42.660 --> 00:05:44.700
I the Lord.

00:05:44.700 --> 00:05:47.899
It's all about him, not about you.

00:05:47.899 --> 00:05:49.100
It's not about what you can do,

00:05:49.100 --> 00:05:51.619
it's about what he can do through you.

00:05:51.619 --> 00:05:53.700
Isn't that an encouragement tonight?

00:05:53.700 --> 00:05:55.980
It's all about God.

00:05:55.980 --> 00:05:58.660
And that takes the pressure off us, doesn't it?

00:05:58.660 --> 00:06:00.980
We were going out soul winning yesterday.

00:06:00.980 --> 00:06:02.859
And sometimes we can get a little bit depressed

00:06:02.859 --> 00:06:05.940
and discouraged because nobody answers the door.

00:06:05.940 --> 00:06:07.540
Maybe that happens, I know that happens here

00:06:07.540 --> 00:06:08.820
because your pastor said that,

00:06:08.820 --> 00:06:11.260
but it happens sometimes where we are in Wales.

00:06:11.260 --> 00:06:13.980
Nobody answers the door, nobody's interested.

00:06:13.980 --> 00:06:16.700
Listen, it's not about you or about me.

00:06:16.700 --> 00:06:20.859
It's about the Lord and what the Lord's doing.

00:06:20.859 --> 00:06:23.140
And I just want to look at this text tonight.

00:06:23.140 --> 00:06:25.700
Here were people who were in captivity

00:06:25.700 --> 00:06:28.779
and they needed to see the Lord.

00:06:28.779 --> 00:06:30.500
You need to see the Lord.

00:06:30.500 --> 00:06:31.660
I need to see the Lord.

00:06:31.660 --> 00:06:33.619
It's all the Lord tonight.

00:06:33.619 --> 00:06:35.779
And let's just look at this very quickly.

00:06:35.820 --> 00:06:39.299
The Bible tells us this expression, I the Lord,

00:06:39.299 --> 00:06:43.100
or just the word I is found in this text six times.

00:06:43.100 --> 00:06:46.179
Look at verse 17, I the Lord will hear them.

00:06:46.179 --> 00:06:48.459
I the God of Israel will not forsake them.

00:06:48.459 --> 00:06:51.619
Verse 18, I will open rivers.

00:06:51.619 --> 00:06:55.380
Then through verse 18, I will make the wilderness.

00:06:55.380 --> 00:06:57.459
Verse 19, I will plant.

00:06:57.459 --> 00:07:00.420
Look at verse number 19, I will set.

00:07:00.420 --> 00:07:02.940
This whole chapter, this whole section

00:07:02.940 --> 00:07:04.380
that we're going to look at tonight

00:07:04.380 --> 00:07:06.700
isn't really about man, it's about God.

00:07:08.059 --> 00:07:10.700
And when you have a high view of who God is

00:07:10.700 --> 00:07:12.459
and what he's doing,

00:07:12.459 --> 00:07:14.899
then that changes everything for you, doesn't it?

00:07:16.019 --> 00:07:18.739
So here is our text this evening.

00:07:18.739 --> 00:07:20.299
The first thing I want you to notice

00:07:20.299 --> 00:07:25.179
is that here are a people who are dwelling,

00:07:25.179 --> 00:07:26.579
this is a prophecy obviously,

00:07:26.579 --> 00:07:30.019
but are dwelling amidst captivity,

00:07:30.019 --> 00:07:33.339
who have nothing, but they have the Lord.

00:07:34.220 --> 00:07:35.980
Notice of their condition.

00:07:35.980 --> 00:07:37.619
The first point this evening is this really,

00:07:37.619 --> 00:07:39.260
I the Lord hears.

00:07:39.260 --> 00:07:40.660
Notice their condition.

00:07:40.660 --> 00:07:45.260
When the poor and needy seek water.

00:07:45.260 --> 00:07:47.540
Now we could spend a whole sermon tonight

00:07:47.540 --> 00:07:49.100
talking about those two names, couldn't we?

00:07:49.100 --> 00:07:51.019
Poor and needy.

00:07:51.940 --> 00:07:56.940
Poor meaning afflicted, wrecked, weak, humbled.

00:07:57.140 --> 00:08:00.059
I wonder tonight, have you ever been humbled in your life?

00:08:01.019 --> 00:08:03.619
Have you got to a place where God has taken

00:08:03.619 --> 00:08:06.700
everything away from you apart from himself?

00:08:07.940 --> 00:08:10.899
These people, they were poor,

00:08:10.899 --> 00:08:12.700
but not only were they poor, look at it,

00:08:12.700 --> 00:08:15.940
they were needy, they were in want, they needed help.

00:08:17.859 --> 00:08:19.820
And do you know, the Bible tells us

00:08:19.820 --> 00:08:22.820
who's the first person who hears the cry

00:08:22.820 --> 00:08:24.859
of the poor and needy?

00:08:24.859 --> 00:08:26.220
It isn't Isaiah.

00:08:27.220 --> 00:08:30.779
Who's the first person who's heard the cries

00:08:30.779 --> 00:08:33.859
of those in Africa tonight, or those in America,

00:08:33.859 --> 00:08:36.020
those on your own street who are desperate

00:08:36.020 --> 00:08:37.219
for the word of God?

00:08:37.219 --> 00:08:40.020
Who is the one that hears their cry?

00:08:40.020 --> 00:08:41.260
It's I the Lord.

00:08:42.179 --> 00:08:46.059
Before you ever go and reach someone with the gospel,

00:08:46.059 --> 00:08:49.179
God is already seeking them, isn't that wonderful?

00:08:49.179 --> 00:08:51.140
It's all I the Lord.

00:08:51.140 --> 00:08:53.979
It all begins with I the Lord, isn't that wonderful?

00:08:53.979 --> 00:08:55.539
And look what they're looking for.

00:08:56.099 --> 00:08:58.219
Very basic provision.

00:08:58.219 --> 00:09:01.739
When the poor and needy seek water.

00:09:01.739 --> 00:09:05.500
Now we live in the Western part of the world, don't we?

00:09:05.500 --> 00:09:07.380
Western civilization.

00:09:07.380 --> 00:09:09.859
And England isn't much different,

00:09:09.859 --> 00:09:11.099
you may be surprised to say this,

00:09:11.099 --> 00:09:13.099
but England's much, much different than America.

00:09:13.099 --> 00:09:15.900
We have taps just like you do here and all those things.

00:09:15.900 --> 00:09:17.859
I remember one time I met someone who said,

00:09:17.859 --> 00:09:19.739
do you all have internet in England?

00:09:19.739 --> 00:09:20.780
We do.

00:09:20.780 --> 00:09:23.460
And we have taps just like everyone else does.

00:09:23.460 --> 00:09:25.340
We're a Western civilization.

00:09:26.140 --> 00:09:28.820
Water is a very basic need, isn't it?

00:09:28.820 --> 00:09:32.940
And here were people who were reduced to nothing.

00:09:32.940 --> 00:09:35.099
They had absolutely nothing.

00:09:35.099 --> 00:09:37.619
They didn't even have water.

00:09:37.619 --> 00:09:39.659
Look what they were seeking for it.

00:09:39.659 --> 00:09:40.619
They were looking for it.

00:09:40.619 --> 00:09:43.700
Can you imagine just for a moment here this evening,

00:09:43.700 --> 00:09:45.460
being in this part of the world

00:09:45.460 --> 00:09:48.700
and not having the provision of water?

00:09:48.700 --> 00:09:50.539
Having no tap to turn on,

00:09:50.539 --> 00:09:52.539
having no bottle to drink out of the fridge

00:09:52.539 --> 00:09:54.940
of cool, refreshing water.

00:09:55.539 --> 00:09:57.700
But this isn't talking about physical provision.

00:09:57.700 --> 00:09:59.500
I want to apply this spiritually.

00:09:59.500 --> 00:10:04.699
There are many people around the world today who do not have what you have.

00:10:04.699 --> 00:10:08.300
They don't have the freedom to worship God like you do.

00:10:08.300 --> 00:10:11.300
They don't have a gospel preacher like you do,

00:10:11.300 --> 00:10:13.300
who takes the Word of God and preaches it.

00:10:13.300 --> 00:10:15.899
And can I tell you, the country that I've come from

00:10:15.899 --> 00:10:18.500
is full of history of men and women like that.

00:10:18.500 --> 00:10:21.299
But today, the sad reality is,

00:10:21.299 --> 00:10:25.100
there are many people that don't have spiritual water.

00:10:25.100 --> 00:10:28.299
We have people in our church, in our video, we showed it to you,

00:10:28.299 --> 00:10:32.700
who travel 50 miles one way and 50 miles the other way on a Sunday

00:10:32.700 --> 00:10:35.099
just to come to worship with people

00:10:35.099 --> 00:10:38.700
who love the Word of God being preached as it should be preached.

00:10:38.700 --> 00:10:40.099
Can you imagine that?

00:10:40.099 --> 00:10:43.700
50 miles one way with five children in the car,

00:10:43.700 --> 00:10:46.700
and 50 miles back, they stay all day?

00:10:46.700 --> 00:10:49.700
That's how serious people were for the Word of God.

00:10:49.700 --> 00:10:53.099
And here are people tonight, and they haven't got water,

00:10:53.099 --> 00:10:55.700
there is none, their tongue's failing for thirst,

00:10:55.700 --> 00:11:00.099
they begin to get desperate, then God hears them and steps in.

00:11:00.099 --> 00:11:02.500
And I tell you tonight, the sad reality is,

00:11:02.500 --> 00:11:06.900
we don't really ever see the Lord until we really need to see Him.

00:11:06.900 --> 00:11:11.699
Until we start to get desperate for God.

00:11:11.699 --> 00:11:16.699
Do you know the danger of living in a country like the United Kingdom,

00:11:16.699 --> 00:11:21.099
in a country like America, I'm assuming tonight, I'm a guest here,

00:11:21.099 --> 00:11:25.099
but is that we can get so comfortable with everything,

00:11:25.099 --> 00:11:28.500
we don't realize we need God.

00:11:28.500 --> 00:11:33.099
We're so used to the mechanics of Christianity even,

00:11:33.099 --> 00:11:35.900
we're so used to the blessings of coming into a meeting

00:11:35.900 --> 00:11:39.500
and going out again and doing that Sunday after Sunday,

00:11:39.500 --> 00:11:44.300
we forget one key thing, we need God.

00:11:44.300 --> 00:11:47.099
We need the Lord.

00:11:47.099 --> 00:11:49.500
And that's what these people were reduced to.

00:11:49.500 --> 00:11:53.300
They were reduced to people who were hopeless, who were helpless,

00:11:53.500 --> 00:11:56.099
listen, they didn't have water.

00:11:56.099 --> 00:12:00.699
They were seeking water, they couldn't find it.

00:12:00.699 --> 00:12:04.500
But I, the Lord, stepped in.

00:12:04.500 --> 00:12:06.699
Isn't that wonderful?

00:12:06.699 --> 00:12:10.500
Look what it says here in our text in verse 17.

00:12:10.500 --> 00:12:13.500
They thirst, their tongue's failing for thirst,

00:12:13.500 --> 00:12:17.699
but I, the Lord, will hear them.

00:12:17.699 --> 00:12:21.100
Can I tell you, in the nation of Wales,

00:12:21.100 --> 00:12:25.300
there were Christians, a group of five people in a little town

00:12:25.300 --> 00:12:28.500
called Welshpool, who were desperate for God

00:12:28.500 --> 00:12:33.500
to do something with their chapel building.

00:12:33.500 --> 00:12:39.500
And they didn't contact us first, God heard them.

00:12:39.500 --> 00:12:41.699
And that's always the way it works, isn't it?

00:12:41.699 --> 00:12:45.699
You may be here tonight, and you may need to know this,

00:12:45.699 --> 00:12:47.300
I need to know this, listen,

00:12:47.300 --> 00:12:54.300
what we really need is God to do something, not us.

00:12:54.300 --> 00:12:56.100
Do you know, in the United Kingdom,

00:12:56.100 --> 00:13:00.899
you can't convince anyone to be a Christian as it were.

00:13:00.899 --> 00:13:04.899
It's hard, it's difficult, people are stubborn to it.

00:13:04.899 --> 00:13:06.899
People don't want anything to do with the Lord things,

00:13:06.899 --> 00:13:08.699
and maybe it's the same here.

00:13:08.699 --> 00:13:10.300
What do we need?

00:13:10.300 --> 00:13:14.300
We need what Isaiah needed, we need I, the Lord,

00:13:14.300 --> 00:13:18.899
to open the hearts and the eyes of the hearts of the men and women of the people,

00:13:18.899 --> 00:13:21.300
and God is doing that.

00:13:21.300 --> 00:13:22.899
He hasn't changed.

00:13:22.899 --> 00:13:26.100
He's the same yesterday, today, and forever.

00:13:26.100 --> 00:13:28.300
And just as people are poor and needy,

00:13:28.300 --> 00:13:31.899
listen, it's a good place when a nation gets poor and needy,

00:13:31.899 --> 00:13:35.300
because then I, the Lord, works.

00:13:35.300 --> 00:13:37.500
And maybe in this church tonight,

00:13:37.500 --> 00:13:39.300
maybe I can encourage you by saying this,

00:13:39.300 --> 00:13:44.899
listen, God is doing something in your location, in your locality.

00:13:44.899 --> 00:13:47.500
